ences==\n*[http://www.mlssoccer.com/stats/1998/reg MLS Site]\n\n{{Major League Soccer}}\n{{1998 MLS season by team}}\n{{Major League Soccer seasons}}\n{{1998 in American soccer}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1998 Major League Soccer Season}}\n[[Category:1998 Major League Soccer season| ]]\n[[Category:1998 in American soccer leagues]]\n[[Category:Major League Soccer seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Use American English|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox football league season\n  | season                     = '''1998'''\n  | mlscup                     = [[Chicago Fire (soccer)|Chicago Fire]] (1st title)\n  | shield                     = [[Los Angeles Galaxy]] (1st shield)\n  | league topscorer           = [[Stern John]]<br>(26 goals)\n  | matches                    = 192\n  | total goals                = 701\n  | average goals              = \n  | biggest home win           =\n  | biggest away win           = \n  | highest scoring            =\n  | longest wins               = [[Chicago Fire (soccer)|Chicago Fire]]<br>Games: 11<br>(05/16 \u2013 07/09)\n  | longest unbeaten           =\n  | longest losses             = [[New England Revolution]]<br>Games: 9<br>(05/13 \u2013 07/04)\n  | highest attendance         = [[Los Angeles Galaxy]]<br>Season: 348,549<br>Game Avg.: 21,784 \n  | lowest attendance          = [[Kansas City Wizards]]<br>Season: 129,163<br>Game Avg.: 8,073\n  | attendance                 = 2,747,897\n  | average attendance         = 14,312\n  | prevseason                 = [[1997 Major League Soccer season|1997]]\n  | nextseason                 = [[1999 Major League Soccer season|1999]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1998 Major League Soccer season''' was the third season of [[Major League Soccer]]. [[Chicago Fire Soccer Club|Chicago Fire]] and [[Miami Fusion F.C.|Miami Fusion]] played their inaugural seasons as the first two MLS expansion teams.  Chicago would become the first expansion team to win the MLS Cup and the first to win it in the inaugural year.\n\n==Final standings==\n\n*3 points were awarded for a win.\n*1 point was awarded for a shootout win and considered a win in the standings.\n*No points were awarded for a loss or a shootout loss, with the latter being considered a loss in the standings\n*The top four teams in each conference advanced to the playoffs.\n\n===Eastern Conference===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!width=\"170\"|Eastern Conference\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| P | Played}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| W | Total Wins}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| SW |Shootout Wins}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| SL |Shootout Losses}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| L | Total Losses}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| WIR | Wins in Regulation}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| SO | Shootouts (Ties in Regulation)}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| LIR | Losses in Regulation}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| GF | Goals For}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| GA | Goals Against}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| GD | Goal Difference}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| APts | Adjusted Points (WIR x 3 + SO)}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| Pts | Points (WIR x 3 + SW)}}\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n|align=left|[[D.C. United]]\n|32||24||7||3||8||17||10||5||74||48||26||61||'''58'''\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n|align=left|[[Columbus Crew]]\n|32||15||0||5||17||15||5||12||67||56||11||50||'''45'''\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n|align=left|[[MetroStars]]\n|32||15||3||4||17||12||7||13||54||63||-9||43||'''39'''\n|- style=\"background:#cfc;\"\n|align=left|[[Miami Fusion F.C.|Miami Fusion]]\n|32||15||5||0||17||10||5||17||46||68||-22||35||'''35'''\n|-\n|align=left|[[Tampa Bay Mutiny]]\n|32||12||1||5||20||11||6||15||46||57||-11||39||'''34'''\n|-\n|align=left|[[New England Revolution]]\n|32||11||2||4||21||9||6||17||53||66|66||-13||33\n|'''29'''\n|}\n\n===Western Conference===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!width=\"170\"|Western Conference\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| P | Played}}\n!width=\"40\"|{{Tooltip| W | Total Wins}}\n!width=\"40\"|{